# Blog post creation SOP

Before creating or substantially editing any post under `content/posts/`,
**read `content/CONTENT-STRATEGY.md`** and follow it. It is the source of truth.

Key points (full detail in the SOP):

- Two content types via `contentType` frontmatter:
  - `implementation` (primary): installable workflow guide. Always follow the
    canonical section order: intro hook (no heading), `## Available resources`
    (+ `<WorkflowDownload />`), `## What you'll need`, `## Overview of the automation`
    (+ `<WorkflowDiagram />`), `## Step-by-step setup` (`###` subsections: data store,
    credentials, phase one, phase two, import JSON), `## Testing the workflow`,
    `## Customization options`, `## Common mistakes that quietly break this`,
    `<InlineCta />`, `## Conclusion`. Reference posts:
    `implement-ai-form-replies-human-in-the-loop` and
    `linkedin-post-automation-ai-agents-n8n`.
  - `playbook` (secondary): architecture and research. Problem, target architecture,
    components, human-in-the-loop, data model, guardrails.
- Pair related posts with `companionSlug` on both (playbook <-> implementation).
- Usual order: ship the playbook first, then the implementation guide.
- Start from `content/templates/playbook-post.template.mdx` or
  `content/templates/implementation-post.template.mdx`.
- Validate frontmatter against `lib/content/schema.ts` (title 8-120, description 40-200,
  kebab-case slug, one of the eight categories in `lib/content/categories.ts`).
- Every CTA points to `siteConfig.agency.bookCallUrl` (Cal.com).
- Do not add `<CtaBlock />` in post MDX. The post layout picks the CTA from `contentType`:
  `implementation` → "Need help setting this up?"; `playbook` → "Want this built for you?".
- For architecture diagrams use the `<WorkflowDiagram />` MDX component, never ASCII art.
- No em dashes or en dashes. No invented stats (use `TODO(stat)`). Brand casing:
  "n8n Automation Hub" and "FusionSync AI".
- Run `npm run check:rules` and `npm run typecheck` before considering a post done.
